      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(configure): migrate stale Codex defaults after OpenAI auth",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhat problem does this PR solve?\n\n- Fixes a configure/auth mismatch where OpenAI ChatGPT/Codex auth could preserve a stale legacy `codex/gpt-5.5` default while adding the canonical `openai/gpt-5.5` model.\n- Keeps the selected primary model aligned with the canonical OpenAI provider id returned by auth.\n\nWhy does this matter now?\n\n- Issue #88456 reports successful ChatGPT/Codex device pairing followed by config returning to the menu with an unusable default model outside the selected provider model set.\n\nWhat is the intended outcome?\n\n- After OpenAI/Codex auth returns `openai/gpt-5.5`, a matching stale `codex/gpt-5.5` or `openai-codex/gpt-5.5` primary is migrated to `openai/gpt-5.5` instead of being preserved.\n- Existing default preservation is unchanged for unrelated providers.\n\nWhat is intentionally out of scope?\n\n- This does not redesign the OpenAI/Codex model picker or change live OAuth/device-code transport.\n- This does not remove legacy model-map entries; it only prevents a matching stale legacy ref from remaining the primary default.\n\nWhat does success look like?\n\n- The configured primary model is present under the canonical OpenAI model entry after auth.\n- Existing non-OpenAI defaults are still preserved when provider auth only adds another available model.\n\nWhat should reviewers focus on?\n\n- The preserve-existing-default guard in `src/plugins/provider-auth-choice.ts`.\n- The regression test proving `codex/gpt-5.5` migrates to `openai/gpt-5.5` only for the matching OpenAI auth path.\n\n## Linked context\n\nWhich issue does this close?\n\nCloses #88456\n\nWhich issues, PRs, or discussions are related?\n\nRelated #88456\n\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner?\n\n- No direct maintainer request beyond the linked issue.\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: OpenAI/Codex auth no longer leaves a matching stale legacy Codex ref as the default primary while canonical OpenAI refs are added to the model map.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on this branch, invoking the actual provider-auth config application path with a redacted local token/provider setup.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: Ran the auth-choice config application path directly with before primary `codex/gpt-5.5`, selected auth model `openai/gpt-5.5`, and `preserveExistingDefaultModel: true`.\n- Evidence after fix (screenshot, recording, terminal capture, console output, redacted runtime log, linked artifact, or copied live output):\n  Terminal transcript:\n  ```text\n  $ COREPACK_HOME=/home/node/.cache/corepack PNPM_HOME=/home/node/.local/share/pnpm node --import tsx --input-type=module\n  {\n    \"beforePrimary\": \"codex/gpt-5.5\",\n    \"afterPrimary\": \"openai/gpt-5.5\",\n    \"allowlistKeys\": [\n      \"codex/gpt-5.5\",\n      \"openai/gpt-5.5\"\n    ],\n    \"note\": {\n      \"title\": \"Model configured\",\n      \"message\": \"Default model set to openai/gpt-5.5\"\n    }\n  }\n  ```\n- Observed result after fix: The primary default changes to canonical `openai/gpt-5.5` while both legacy and canonical model entries remain present in `agents.defaults.models`.\n- What was not tested: A full live ChatGPT/Codex device-code browser pairing against a real account from this container.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: The worker cannot complete the interactive account authorization step without a user/browser handoff. The proof exercises the same config mutation path after auth returns a canonical OpenAI default.\n- Before evidence (optional but encouraged): The linked issue shows the broken state: primary `codex/gpt-5.5` with canonical OpenAI entries in the model allowlist.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\nWhich commands did you run?\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.commands.config.ts src/commands/auth-choice.apply.plugin-provider.test.ts src/commands/configure.gateway-auth.prompt-auth-config.test.ts --maxWorkers=1`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check src/plugins/provider-auth-choice.ts src/commands/auth-choice.apply.plugin-provider.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core:test`\n\nWhat regression coverage was added or updated?\n\n- Added provider-auth coverage for `preserveExistingDefaultModel: true` with existing primary `codex/gpt-5.5` and OpenAI auth default `openai/gpt-5.5`.\n- The test verifies the primary is migrated to `openai/gpt-5.5`, the canonical model entry is present, and the provider selection hook still runs.\n\nWhat failed before this fix, if known?\n\n- The stale legacy default could be preserved as primary even though OpenAI auth added canonical `openai/*` entries, leaving the session default outside the selected provider allowlist.\n\nIf no test was added, why not?\n\n- Not applicable; regression coverage was added.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nYes\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nYes\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nNo\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n\n- The preserve-existing-default behavior during provider auth.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n\n- The new exception is narrow: it only applies when OpenAI auth returns an `openai/*` model and the previous primary is a matching legacy `codex/*` or `openai-codex/*` ref for the same model id.\n- Existing coverage still verifies unrelated existing defaults remain preserved.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n\n- Maintainer review.\n\nWhat is still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof?\n\n- CI.\n- Optional maintainer/live-environment confirmation of the full ChatGPT/Codex device-code prompt flow.\n\nWhich bot or reviewer comments were addressed?\n\n- Initial Real behavior proof gate failure was addressed by replacing prose-only evidence with copied terminal output.\n",
